The paper discusses the comparison of algorithms for robotic swarms and general multi-robot systems in two application domains, navigation and dynamic area coverage. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of local information and emergent collective behaviors, which are key features of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of control laws and mission constraints, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The comparison of algorithms is based on metrics such as completion time and distance travelled, which are related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
